TI  - Economies of Scale in Services: A study of Multinational Insurers
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 305
EP  - 323
VL  - 29
IS  - 2
AB  - This study investigates whether multinational insurers achieve economies of scale. Using a time-series, cross-sectional design, it analyzes the relationship between expenses and output of multinational insurers. The study finds that multinational insurers achieve economies of scale only up to a point, and rather than benefitting from scale, the most internationally diverse insurers suffer diseconomies. The conclusion is that the benefits of extensive foreign acquisitions by insurers are questionable.
